#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:122
msgid "Feature: New expression functions in 2.12"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:124
msgid ""
"A set of functions for \\\"fuzzy matching\\\" have been added. These include"
" functions for finding the similarity of two strings and also for performing"
" phonetic matching between strings, and allow you to perform filters for "
"records which \\\"nearly match\\\" a specified string."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:126
msgid "More geometry based functions have been added, including:"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:128
msgid "`num_points(geom)` for calculating the number of nodes in a geometry"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:129
msgid ""
"`area(geom)`, `length(geom)` and `perimeter(geom)`, for calculating the "
"area, length and perimeter of any geometry object. Previously only "
"calculation of the area, length and perimeter of the current feature\\'s "
"geometry was possible."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:130
msgid ""
"`start_point(geom)`, `end_point(geom)`, `point_n(geom, n)`, for retrieving "
"the first, last and numbered points from a geometry"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:131
msgid "`make_point(x,y)`, for manual creation of a point geometry"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:132
msgid ""
"`x(geom)`, `y(geom)` functions which return the x and y coordinate for point"
" geometries or the centroid x/y for non-point geometries"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:134
msgid ""
"A new `project_color` function has been added, which allows you to retrieve "
"a color from the project\\'s color scheme by name. This lets you create "
"\\'linked colors\\', where the color of symbol or labeling components can be"
" bound to a color in the project\\'s color scheme. Update the color in the "
"scheme, and all the linked colors will be automatically refreshed to match!"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:136
msgid ""
"Additionally, some very useful expressions have been ported from the "
"expressions+ plugin, including:"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:138
msgid ""
"`color_part`: allows retreival of a specific color component (eg red, hue, "
"alpha) from a color"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:139
msgid ""
"`set_color_part`: allows a specific color component to be overridden, eg "
"alter the alpha value (opacity) of a color"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:140
msgid "`day_of_week`: returns the day of week as a number from a date"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:142
msgid ""
