#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:334
msgid "Feature: Control priority of labeling obstacles"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:336
msgid ""
"In 2.12 it\\'s now possible to specify the priority for labeling obstacles. "
"This allows you to make labels prefer to overlap features from certain "
"layers rather than others. The priority can also be data defined so that "
"certain features are more likely to be covered than others. You can also use"
" data defined expressions or fields to control whether a specific feature in"
" layer will act as an obstacle for labels."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:340
msgid ""
"![image21](images/entries/f07a082bd4e62f059788c18a9de353107b8bdc44.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:342
msgid "Feature: New options to control how polygon layers act as obstacles"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:344
msgid ""
"New options have been added to control how labels should be placed to avoid "
"overlapping the features in polygon layers. The options are to either avoid "
"placing labels over polygon interiors or avoid placing them over polygon "
"boundaries. Avoiding placing labels over boundaries is useful for regional "
"boundary layers, where the features cover an entire area. In this case "
"it\\'s impossible to avoid placing labels within these features and it looks"
" much better to avoid placing them over the boundaries between features "
"instead. The result is better cartographic placement of labels in this "
"situation."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:350
msgid ""
"![image22](images/entries/e37943c654080e33219acb5e519970cf748c87bf.png)"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:352
msgid "Feature: Data defined control over label priority"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:354
msgid ""
"This often-requested feature allows users to set the priority for individual"
" labels. In past releases QGIS allowed setting the label priority for an "
"entire layer, but there was no option to control the priority of features "
"within a layer. Now, you can use a data defined expression or field to "
"prioritize labeling certain features over others within a layer!"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:356
msgid ""
"See [this article](http://nyalldawson.net/2015/07/recent-labelling-"
"improvements-in-qgis-master/) for more details"
msgstr ""

