msgid "Feature: Data defined control over map layers and style presets"
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:454
msgid ""
"A new data defined control has been added for the map layers and style "
"presets to show in a composer map. The map layers data defined expression "
"should result in a \\| (pipe) delimited list of layer names which will be "
"shown in the map, or the style preset data defined expression should result "
"in the name of an existing style preset."
msgstr ""

#: content/project/visual-changelogs/visualchangelog212/index.md:456
msgid ""
"Using this control over map layers allows for \\\"layer-based\\\" atlases, "
"where the map layers should change between atlas pages instead of or in "
"combination with the map extent changing. An example could be an atlas "
"looping over different administrative units and at the same time looping "
"over several historic maps or aerial images."
msgstr ""

